         <div type="apparatus">
            <p>Waddington suggested <foreign xml:lang="grc">καὶ σοφιστὴν</foreign> for the tenth line, on a parallel with <ref type="inscription" n="1795" target="140018.xml"/> (=LBW 1598bis); but 'rhetor' appears alone in <ref type="inscription" n="1585" target="120909.xml"/> (=CIG 2845), and it is also possible that the text is complete.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>The homeland (set up a statue of) Tiberius Cl(audius) Aurelius Ktesias, son of Tiberius Claudius Kapitoleinos, the rhetor [...]</p>
